{"pageProps":{"article":{"id":"8796e71d5a","title":"尼克松和基辛格的电话谈话记录","origin":"","is_range_date":false,"dates":[{"id":"522f2a28ea","index":0,"year":1971,"month":4,"day":27,"articleId":"8796e71d5a"}],"tags":[{"id":"314ad57c4d","name":"对话","type":"文稿类型"},{"id":"4597fe4abe","name":"越南战争","type":"主题/事件"},{"id":"aa9434abe4","name":"北京文革","type":"人物"},{"id":"d20738c862","name":"世界形势","type":"主题/事件"}],"aliases":[],"publications":[{"id":"GPCRv3","name":"中国文化大革命文库（第三版）","internal":true,"official":false,"type":"db","author":"宋永毅","files":""}],"authors":[]},"publication_details":{"GPCRv3":{"comments":[],"contents":[{"id":"b22647e11a","type":"title","text":"尼克松和基辛格的电话谈话记录","index":0,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"e0b8addb88","type":"appellation","text":"日　　期：\t1971年4月27日","index":1,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"422d6f4985","type":"appellation","text":"时　　间：\t晚上8时18分","index":2,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"cd5207b248","type":"appellation","text":"文　　件：\t尼克松和基辛格的电话谈话记录 — “讨论来自周（恩来）的信息以及可能派往中国的特使”","index":3,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"153f2c39bd","type":"appellation","text":"文件性质：\t备忘录","index":4,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"6a15b20a22","type":"appellation","text":"资料来源：\tNSC Files, Box 1031, Exchanges Leading up to HAK Trip to China, December 1969-July 1971 (1), Nixon Presidential Material Project, 美国第二国家档案馆。","index":5,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"54c22ca76b","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：在这方面我有几个想法。第一，是关于布鲁斯1 的事，我看起来可能会给他们出一些难题，因为他曾经直接参与了越南谈判。其次，让我考虑一下，是不是还有别的人选……纳尔逊2 怎么样？","index":6,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"8fc7fa304b","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：不成。","index":7,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"98a14f8d04","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：难道他不行？","index":8,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c5377002b5","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：总统先生，虽然他是候选对象，但他的纪律观念不强。","index":9,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c8dbd6aba9","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：这将会把他卷入重大的事件中，而且他不在政府工作，是吧？","index":10,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"5a0f6c8be3","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：让我想想看，我或许有能力管住他。","index":11,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"0c90f732d1","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：这是不是令人感兴趣，你认为不是吗？","index":12,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"a357391935","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：这令人感兴趣。","index":13,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"01991ffc40","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：布什3 怎么样？","index":14,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"2934197fe2","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：绝对不可以，他太软弱和不够老练。","index":15,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"35cc5e8711","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：我自己也是这样想。","index":16,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"2c7db32a70","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我曾经考虑过理查森4，但他也不是一个适合的人选。","index":17,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"2a27400fe6","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：他仍然与我们太亲近（我认为他不会与罗杰斯有良好的工作关系）。纳尔逊 — 中国人认为他是重要的，而他将会是重要的 — 能够为我们做很多国内事务。不行，纳尔逊到处惹是生非。","index":18,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c878881763","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我认为做一件事情之后就能够控制他。对他们来说，洛克菲勒家族的人是了不起的。","index":19,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"d578d85c44","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：是的。好吧。把它忘记吧。","index":20,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b50d299612","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：布什可能太软弱了。","index":21,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c7b5701422","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：我也是这么想的，但我试图去考虑一些有资格的人。","index":22,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"1230b06e49","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：可以考虑纳尔逊。","index":23,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"25f7db5148","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：是的，可以考虑。当然，那将会令国务院非常气愤。","index":24,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"94fce39dd0","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：他会从国务院挑选某个人跟随他，但他非常看不起国务院的人，他会接受我们的指导而从我的工作人员中选派一个人跟随他。","index":25,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"89d44dbcc1","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：选派黑格，真的，他真的很过硬。","index":26,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"9e6fce9d98","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：他是认识黑格的。","index":27,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b7418c4875","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：亨利，如果你不固执己见，这件事就不可能发生。我们在玩一种游戏并且我们已得到了一点突破。这件事处理得很巧妙，我们现在要等待一两个星期。","index":28,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b3eb41da01","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：这件事我们现在已经处理好了，我们已经把所有事情套在一起。柏林已被套在了“限制战略武器会谈”上。纳尔逊可能有能力处理这件事情，特别是如果我派出黑格的话。","index":29,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"26c341938f","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：噢，我们应该派出黑格和国务院的某个人，但不是名叫格林的那个人。","index":30,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"76a5dd3ded","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：噢，格林可以去。在外交政策方面，纳尔逊会听我的建议。","index":31,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"5bbeeae23a","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：在某种意义上说，他将会是一位特使。","index":32,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"27d83bb6d8","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：总统先生，实际上，最初的想法就是那样的，他是过硬的。","index":33,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"7a80480a38","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：特别是如果你将他带到山顶上，然后对他说，看，孩子，它会成就你也会毁了你。","index":34,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"53dc5910eb","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：噢，他会做的，在这方面我有把握这么说。对于长时间的","index":35,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"70d1f1a24a","type":"appellation","text":"工作而言，他将会失控，但这一次，他会处理好的。","index":36,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"85cc312743","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：如果杜威还活着的话，他会处理好的。","index":37,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"bcf5d20283","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：纳尔逊可能处理得更好。","index":38,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"8dbbf8cb49","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：但是杜威死了。","index":39,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"52c2e70694","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：如果你能等一会的话，我告诉你 — 我有一份巴基斯坦人转给我的口述便条。在这里 — 这张给叶海亚的巴基斯坦便条已转交给中国人，这张便条要求他（读出便条的一部分 — 作为对我问题的回答，基辛格先生说……）。","index":40,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"314a1b605c","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：他们以谈论台湾问题开始。","index":41,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"f969786aec","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：这些含糊不清的陈述能够在意见交流和公告弄清楚。","index":42,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b9cbe3b1b6","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：他们谈论台湾的答复还没有到这。由于没有会谈，所以对此没有限制。","index":43,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"669c0a4e84","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：他们与俄罗斯人不同之处是：如果你有些零钱掉在地上，当你伸手想把它拾起来时，俄罗斯人会用脚踩住你的手，而中国人不会这样做。我审查过所有与他们的通讯记录，该口信来自高层。","index":44,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b9c22f0102","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：是的，它来自高层。","index":45,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"7e7e78260a","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：俄罗斯人总要压制我们的每一步行动，这样做是极其愚蠢的。他们不能哄骗我们离开台湾，他们得有一点基本认识。","index":46,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"51984811fb","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：纳尔逊不在考虑之列。黑格对此是怎么考虑的？","index":47,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"3cc6240fc9","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：他认为这次外交行动非同寻常，如果我们就像现在那样冷静而坚强地对待此事，我们能够解决任何事情。","index":48,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"44c0237637","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：他说得对。","index":49,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"255d215501","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：总统先生，以前我没有说过这样的话，但是我认为如果我们能够使这件事成功的话，我们将会在今年结束越战。实际上，正是这些联系才会有成功。","index":50,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"ca682ae1c3","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：另一件事当然是有关我们的时间安排的小问题。说到什么时候公布……","index":51,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"ebd2677562","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：无论如何，我们应该在六月份的第一个星期之前公布。","index":52,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"047fda94d7","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：如果我们打算在六月份去那里的话，我们必须那么做。“限制战略武器会谈”是否使他们很厌烦？","index":53,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"8b9381f2e3","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：不，不。","index":54,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"975be7a029","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：特别要说的是，如果我们打算和俄罗斯人在高峰会议的问题上不合作的话，他们会在那里瞎忙，是的，就让他们瞎忙吧。","index":55,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"e3b304b30d","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：因为在这个国家有抗议活动，他们行动起来不会太快。周恩来写的报告分析得更为复杂。","index":56,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c48705abc5","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：实际上，他在分析时认识到我们在做什么。","index":57,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"5fdde741ed","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：那是一份对国际形势的精细分析。","index":58,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"7998fc456a","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：不管怎么样，我们也要留住另外一位人选。布鲁斯也是候选对象。把布鲁斯从巴黎调至北京会极具戏剧性。","index":59,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"5020f26ac3","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：为了这个原因，他们可能不接受他。","index":60,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"7357ac05fb","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：就布鲁斯来说，布鲁斯是我们的资深大使，我们认为他是最合格的人选。","index":61,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"da2bdd5be8","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：他们会喜欢洛克菲勒的，他很引人注目。","index":62,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"84da280de5","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：引人注目会起到很大的作用。难道你就不能看到那对这个国家的解放运动起到多大的作用，噢，上帝。洛克菲勒在那，耶稣基督。","index":63,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"07591b84be","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：那有很大的可能性。","index":64,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"ce7dfc3c8b","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：洛克菲勒 — 他总是和我们站在一起，在外交政策上他总是和我们站在一起。不管怎么样，这件事值得考虑一下。","index":65,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"a3c1daeca4","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：值得考虑这个问题。","index":66,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"720003ec35","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：真是值得考虑这个问题。","index":67,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"d06c989be5","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：一旦这件事办好了，所有的事情都会开始协调起来。","index":68,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"1d0cfc9fe3","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：我希望这样。","index":69,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"96ab19756d","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：星期四时你得在越南问题上保持强硬。","index":70,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"a7ced6f82c","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：我本来就想保持强硬的。战俘问题进展得怎么样？","index":71,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"17a490f235","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我有三点建议，正打算写下来 — 他们将会释放一千人、开放他们的战俘营并且要求北越人也这样做，他们也会提议将所有战俘关押在中立国家里。这件事应该由布鲁斯在上午宣布……","index":72,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"75182a1052","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：好的。","index":73,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"56fe29303b","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：晚上你便会知道了。","index":74,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"f43c7bcc92","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：如果我们把它扩大一点的话，他们可能知道我们在干什么。他们都认为这是在准备撤退，但实际上是为了战俘。","index":75,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"62838f58b4","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我们正开始掌握主动。","index":76,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"d79a4cfa26","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：是的，不过我们打算控制局势。那些示威者可能太过火了。","index":77,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"1c849f2927","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我今天与〔时代周刊主编〕约翰．钱赛勒一起吃午饭，他认为潮流已经改变。","index":78,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"3c653089eb","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：什么改变了潮流？","index":79,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"e467952d41","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：他认为，这个星期所发生的事把他们毁了。","index":80,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"1282f9d8ff","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：约翰．钱赛勒……","index":81,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"91006797ae","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：绝对是，他真的不知道你葫芦里卖什么药，但是……","index":82,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"028fa5b014","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：先生们，我不打算谈有关中国的任何事情，除非那些建议处于非常敏感的阶段，否则我也不打算对未来和下一个问题作评论。","index":83,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"eeee38cd75","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：好的。","index":84,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"91109cfbf0","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：我不会涉及到“两个中国”的政策、联合国会员国问题以及台湾等问题的提议。我打算通过说这的进展是明显的来巧妙回答所有的问题，我认为进一步的谈论不符合国家的利益。","index":85,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"5d77765975","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：总统先生，我认为这是采取的最好立场。","index":86,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"16447f6bcf","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：黑格很高兴。","index":87,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"6dbacc4df3","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：如果有人在两个月前预测到这点，我们会认为这是不可想像的。","index":88,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"acf8745b36","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：是的，是的，老挝之后……","index":89,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"6841787980","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：柬埔寨之后，同一件事……","index":90,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"9d8847e1c5","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：是的，不过，在老挝事件后观察，超过二比一的人会认为这件事失败了，现在中国开始行动了，乒乓球队和一些更加有影响力的事情会令这件事黯然失色。这件事可能有很大的影响力。好啦，纳尔逊将这个声明告诉了斯诺，我们怎样才能够让曼斯菲尔德闭上嘴巴。我不知道我们怎样才能做到，但有一个办法可以做到，那就是邀请他一起去。","index":91,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"5cfe7595e5","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：不，为什么邀请他呢？","index":92,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"842f23c068","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：他可以和我一起去。","index":93,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"eeeebd61a3","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：当你去时，他可以和你一起走。","index":94,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"cd3e7d5758","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：我们可以邀请曼斯菲尔德和斯考克罗夫特5。","index":95,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"fd2d4db291","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：如果你想和民主党共享这件事的话。","index":96,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"aadb7da5c3","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：共享吧：中国人会待他们很好的，不过，他们将知道谁掌权。","index":97,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"18938cdf6a","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：实际上，他们还没有邀请过任何人。","index":98,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"9b3ea7d8fb","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：你能够传给他一个信息吗？","index":99,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c45a911ed6","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我认为我可以传给他一个口信。","index":100,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"52fe3c57bf","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：两个星期后，我在想，在那以前他们是否会把曼斯菲尔德赶走。","index":101,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"0ab97c00a9","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：不，但他们可能会。","index":102,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"8c79005732","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：作为一个临时性的举措，你是否可以说总统将会在加利福尼亚并且……","index":103,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c7dec8d756","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我已经告诉他们了，而且一个建设性的答复很快会到。","index":104,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"7815503f4f","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：如果你再补充一点，即在我们答复以前，应该搁置其他任何访问。","index":105,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"af907e5ecd","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：我会把这点向他们讲清楚的。","index":106,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b7984a1d2f","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：将会有许多访问请求，我们认为各种政治上的请求……","index":107,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"b7078ce2bf","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：是的。","index":108,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"092857ba9d","type":"appellation","text":"总  统：好主意，就这样吧，亨利，再见。","index":109,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"a01fd1af10","type":"appellation","text":"基辛格：再见，总统先生。","index":110,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"df2871980c","type":"appellation","text":"注 释","index":111,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"c916e05402","type":"paragraph","text":"1.大卫．布鲁斯David K. E. Bruce（1898-1977），美国资深职业外交官，曾于1949至1952年任驻法大使，1957至1959年任驻西德大使，1961至1969年驻英大使。七十年代初参加美国与北越在巴黎的秘密谈判。中美关系正常化后，尼克松总统1973年任命七十五岁高龄的布鲁斯担任美国驻华联络处首任主任。关于布鲁斯大使出使北京的经历，参看Priscilla Roberts, ed., The Dairy of David Bruce (Hong Kong: Institute of Asian Studies, Hong Kong University, 2000).","index":112,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"0bf4d48c5f","type":"paragraph","text":"2.纳尔逊．洛克菲勒（Nelson Rockefeller）1908年出生于美国巨富约翰．洛克菲勒家中，1958至1973年间四次出任纽约州州长，1964年和1968年","index":113,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"0a03dda1be","type":"appellation","text":"两次参加共和党总统候选人提名的竞争。1977年曾担任福特政府的副总统。","index":114,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"bb43b761b6","type":"paragraph","text":"3.乔治．布什（George Bush）曾担任中央情报局局长，美国驻中国联络处主任，里根政府时期（1981-1989）担任副总统，1989至1993年间为美国总统。","index":115,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"2da7ec3ee5","type":"paragraph","text":"4.理查森指曾任副国务卿的Elliot L. Richardson。参看前面的注释。","index":116,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"71254b1921","type":"paragraph","text":"5.曼斯菲尔德（Michael Mansfield），1953至1976年间任美国国会参议员（民主党），曾一度担任参议院多数党领袖。肯尼迪政府期间，曼斯菲尔德作为总统特使出访南越，回来后建议美国不要介入印度支那。此后，他一直反对美国发动的越南战争。斯考克罗夫特（Brent Scowcroft），美国西点军校毕业，后获得哥伦比亚大学博士学位。长期任职于美国空军，并获少将军衔。1973至1975年间担任总统国家安全事务副助理，1975至1977年间担任助理，1989至1993年间担任布什总统的国家安全顾问。","index":117,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"},{"id":"aae553fcb1","type":"appellation","text":"原载 《中美“解冻”与台湾问题：尼克松外交文献选编》， 香港中文大学出版社，2008年。","index":118,"publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a"}],"page":{"id":"cfb934197c","publicationId":"GPCRv3","articleId":"8796e71d5a","start":0,"end":0}}}},"__N_SSG":true}